Full Dataset analysis v1 - Doublet

Read metadata and embedding coordinate files from analysis-v1

metadata <- read.csv('/data/deprez_data/HCA/Analysis/FullDataset_v1/metadata_doublet.tsv',
                     sep = '\t', header = T, stringsAsFactors = F)

coords <- read.csv('/data/deprez_data/HCA/Analysis/FullDataset_v1/HCA_airway_epithelium_v1/umap_coords.tsv',
                     sep = '\t', header = T, stringsAsFactors = F)

metadata$x <- coords$x
metadata$y <- coords$y
metadata$cell_type <- factor(metadata$cell_type, levels = cell_type_order)
metadata$doubletDetection <- metadata$doubletDetection == 1
metadata$predicted_doublets <- metadata$predicted_doublets == 'True'

Analysis of the identified doublets

Scrublet method

Percentage of doublet per sample

doublet_df <- as.data.frame(table(metadata$manip, metadata$predicted_doublets))
doublet_df <- tidyr::spread(doublet_df, "Var2", "Freq")
rownames(doublet_df) <- doublet_df$Var1
doublet_df <- doublet_df[, c('TRUE', 'FALSE')]
doublet_df$total <- rowSums(doublet_df)
doublet_df$pct_doublet <- doublet_df$'TRUE' / doublet_df$total
doublet_df$Method <- substr(rownames(doublet_df), 6, 9)
doublet_df$Position <- substr(rownames(doublet_df), 11, 13)


ggplot(doublet_df, aes(x = total, y = pct_doublet, shape = Method, color = Position)) +
  geom_point(size = 2) +
  scale_color_manual(values = position_color_short) +
  theme_classic()

cor.test(doublet_df$total, doublet_df$pct_doublet)
## 
##  Pearson's product-moment correlation
## 
## data:  doublet_df$total and doublet_df$pct_doublet
## t = 1.7822, df = 34, p-value = 0.08365
## alternative hypothesis: true correlation is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  -0.04008435  0.56644049
## sample estimates:
##       cor 
## 0.2923007

Differences between Sampling Method : Brushing VS Biopsy

ggplot(doublet_df, aes(x = Method, y = pct_doublet, fill = Method)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  theme_classic()

wilcox.test(doublet_df$pct_doublet[doublet_df$Method == "Biop"], 
            doublet_df$pct_doublet[doublet_df$Method == "Brus"])
## 
##  Wilcoxon rank sum test
## 
## data:  doublet_df$pct_doublet[doublet_df$Method == "Biop"] and doublet_df$pct_doublet[doublet_df$Method == "Brus"]
## W = 190, p-value = 0.1904
## alternative hypothesis: true location shift is not equal to 0

Differences between Position

ggplot(doublet_df, aes(x = Position, y = pct_doublet, fill = Position)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  scale_fill_manual(values = position_color_short) +
  theme_classic()

doublet_df$Position <- factor(doublet_df$Position, levels = c("Nas", "Pro", "Int", "Dis"))

kruskal.test(pct_doublet ~ Position, data = doublet_df)
## 
##  Kruskal-Wallis rank sum test
## 
## data:  pct_doublet by Position
## Kruskal-Wallis chi-squared = 2.5394, df = 3, p-value = 0.4682

Differences between Cell Type

doublet_df <- as.data.frame(table(metadata$cell_type, metadata$predicted_doublets))
doublet_df <- tidyr::spread(doublet_df, "Var2", "Freq")
rownames(doublet_df) <- doublet_df$Var1
doublet_df <- doublet_df[, c('TRUE', 'FALSE')]
doublet_df$total <- rowSums(doublet_df)
doublet_df$pct_doublet <- doublet_df$'TRUE' / doublet_df$total
doublet_df$cell_type <- factor(rownames(doublet_df), levels = cell_type_order)

ggplot(doublet_df, aes(x = cell_type, y = pct_doublet, fill = cell_type))+
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  scale_fill_manual(values = cell_type_color) +
  theme_classic()+
  theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90)
  )

Correlation between cell type size and number of predicted doublet

                                           metadata$predicted_doublets))[24:46, 1]


g1 = ggplot(doublet_df, aes(x = Freq, y = doublet, label = cell_type,  color = cell_type))+

  geom_point(size= 2) +
  scale_color_manual(values = cell_type_color) +
  theme_classic()+
  theme(legend.position = "none")
